object: Eduard Buchner (German pronunciation: [ˈeːduaʁt ˈbuːxnɐ]; 20 May 1860 – 13 August 1917) was a German chemist and zymologist, awarded the 1907 Nobel Prize in Chemistry for his work on fermentation.
Cell-free fermentation, Buchner ring expansion, Büchner–Curtius–Schlotterbeck reaction, Enzymes, Zymase
